cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) because it describes a method for detecting intentional packet drops on the Internet, which is a security concern. It also involves analyzing network traffic and inferring censorship, which are common topics in the field of cryptography and security. 

It could also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) because it deals with detecting packet drops on the Internet and inferring the direction of the drops. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category because the paper mentions using an autoregressive-moving-average (ARMA) model for intervention analysis, which is a statistical method commonly used in time series analysis and forecasting. 

cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category because the paper discusses measuring censorship of Tor directory servers, which are part of a network of anonymous communication channels. 

Finally, cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category because the paper deals with issues of censorship and freedom of information on the Internet, which are social and ethical concerns.
